High-voltage automated systems of many clinical laboratories are capable of carrying out these analyses, but their availability will depend on the production rate of each system.
For TLC, a single peripheral blood sample is generally used, although serial samples may be used to monitor immune response.
For PoCT, a single blood sample is usually taken by skin puncture.
